flow.copy-open-tips: Enter the opening remarks of the Q&A assistant here, and click the auto-generate button to automatically generate the opening remarks
flow.llm-chatter-tips: When the conversation flow gets stuck, trigger the large model to automatically reply
flow.temperature-tips: Control randomness. Lowering the temperature means that the model will generate more repetitive and deterministic responses. Increasing temperature can lead to more unexpected or creative responses. Try adjusting the temperature or Top P, but do not adjust both at the same time.
flow.prologue-tips: In conversational applications, having AI speak first can enhance interaction with users, making them feel more friendly and comfortable.
flow.interrupt-set-tips: Trigger large model AI reply when session flow gets stuck
flow.max-token-tips: Set a limit on the number of tokens each model can respond to. The API supports up to 15000 tokens, which are shared between prompts (including system messages, examples, message history, and user queries) and model responses. A token is approximately 4 characters of typical English text.
flow.topP-tips: Similar to temperature, this controls randomness but uses different methods. Lowering TopP will narrow down the token selection range of the model, making it more likely to choose tokens. Adding TopP will allow the model to choose between high probability and low probability tokens. Try adjusting the temperature or TopP, but do not adjust both at the same time.

rang.P1: 1. Publish to Skill Square: The skill is presented in the skill square. The publisher can further set the visible range.
rang.P2: If the visible range is the current enterprise, only users within the current tenant are visible;
rang.P3: If the visible range is all tenants, then all users of the skill square are visible
rang.P4: 2. Publish to specified users: The skill is not visible in the skills square, and it will be directly published to the user's subscription area. Users can use it in the subscription area without subscribing.
